<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/51001899-martha"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1451844934i/51001899._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/51001899-martha">Martha</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Since Sean Duffy does not really care about his religion unless it affects him by being called a &quot;fenian&quot; I would not say that the Fact that McKinty i<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Since Sean Duffy does not really care about his religion unless it affects him by being called a "fenian" I would not say that the Fact that McKinty is not Catholic himself really takes away any of the credibility. I also think that McKinty wanted Duffy to be a outsider with a more neutral point of view. He does not really care about politics, he only shares information with the reader, never really taking one side or the other.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
