<div id="review_2949917970" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2949917970" />
    <a title="Kylie H" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/25379212-kylie-h"><img alt="Kylie H" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1393325810p2/25379212.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2949917970?book_show_action=true">Oct 22, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kylie H" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kylie H" href="/user/show/25379212-kylie-h">Kylie H</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook 9781306928793" href="/book/show/22720786-the-cold-cold-ground">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/25379212-kylie-h?shelf=crime">crime</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2949917970" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer722663265633385848">My opinion of this book may not be popular, but I think my expectations may have been very high. In terms of the character and storyline it was all a bit take it or leave it for me. I was not very fond of Sean Duffy and the way he went about his business, and I found the outcome of the story somewhat underwhelming.<br/>The saving grace for me was the era and the setting. 1980 Belfast which was a war zone.The height of the IRA, UVF, UDF, Sinn Fein and so forth. It is now gobsmacking to think this all </span>
  <span id="freeText722663265633385848" style="display:none">My opinion of this book may not be popular, but I think my expectations may have been very high. In terms of the character and storyline it was all a bit take it or leave it for me. I was not very fond of Sean Duffy and the way he went about his business, and I found the outcome of the story somewhat underwhelming.<br />The saving grace for me was the era and the setting. 1980 Belfast which was a war zone.The height of the IRA, UVF, UDF, Sinn Fein and so forth. It is now gobsmacking to think this all occurred in my life time and I was fascinated with the descriptions of day to day life in this environment.<br />At this point I will park this series as I have too many others on the go, but perhaps at some stage revisit it, or more based on Ireland and 'The Troubles'.</span>
  <a data-text-id="722663265633385848" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


