<div id="review_3120729494" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3120729494" />
    <a title="Alex Cantone" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/48050946-alex-cantone"><img alt="Alex Cantone" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1479001219p2/48050946.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3120729494?book_show_action=true">Jan 06, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Alex Cantone" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Alex Cantone" href="/user/show/48050946-alex-cantone">Alex Cantone</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781846688225" href="/book/show/13383740-the-cold-cold-ground">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48050946-alex-cantone?shelf=2021-misc-challenge">2021-misc-challenge</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48050946-alex-cantone?shelf=thriller">thriller</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48050946-alex-cantone?shelf=read-2020">read-2020</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48050946-alex-cantone?shelf=aussie-authors">aussie-authors</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48050946-alex-cantone?shelf=read-2020-az-authors">read-2020-az-authors</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3120729494" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3451397850897655443"><i>We signed out a Land Rover and drove up the Shore Road…the rain was heavy, the traffic light. We drove past a fresh bombsite that was, with ruthless efficiency, being bulldozed into a car park. Soon Belfast would be the only city in the world with more parking spaces than cars.</i><br/><br/>Britain, 1981. A public enthralled by the upcoming nuptials of Prince Charles and Lady Diana Spencer. The horse Shergar the favourite to win the Derby, while overseas, an assassination attempt on Pope John-Paul II - all ov</span>
  <span id="freeText3451397850897655443" style="display:none"><i>We signed out a Land Rover and drove up the Shore Road…the rain was heavy, the traffic light. We drove past a fresh bombsite that was, with ruthless efficiency, being bulldozed into a car park. Soon Belfast would be the only city in the world with more parking spaces than cars.</i><br /><br />Britain, 1981. A public enthralled by the upcoming nuptials of Prince Charles and Lady Diana Spencer. The horse Shergar the favourite to win the Derby, while overseas, an assassination attempt on Pope John-Paul II - all overshadowed by the events in Northern Ireland where the IRA hunger-strikers in the Maze Prison are dying, inciting riots on the streets of Belfast. And in the midst of it all, a crime scene: the murder of Tommy Little, a homosexual (illegal in Ireland at the time). But who killed him and why? <br /><br />We are introduced to DS Sean Duffy, recently-posted to Carrickfergus RUC, a small station in the Protestant town, run by Chief Inspector Tom Brennan, with its force of DS ED McCallister, DC McCrabban with his harsh Ballymena accent, FO Matty McBride and foot-in-mouth PC Price. Duffy is a catholic (Fenian) living in Coronation Road, amid gossiping neighbours and a local “enforcer”, Bobby Cameron. <br /><br />The investigation into the murder of Tommy Little brings Duffy into contact with pathologist Dr Laura Cathcart, and there is an immediate attraction but with another murder and chilling clues, the police believe they are facing Northern Ireland’s first serial killer, and, in tracking the victim’s movements a couple of suspects arise. <br /><br />The story is filled with dry dark humour and the rock bands, TV programmes and movies of the era, interesting characters, including my favourite – the Marxist espousing barber. Author <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/12433.Adrian_McKinty" title="Adrian McKinty" rel="nofollow noopener">Adrian McKinty</a> captures the chaos and carnage of hijacked and burning buses, murals of a masked man wielding an AK-47 painted on the walls at the ends of terraces in the Shankill (protestant) Road area, the IRA controlled Falls Road area, patrolled by the British Army on the ground and in the air, the Royal Ulster Constabulary in riot gear, travelling in armour-plated vehicles, dodging the potholes and milk cartons (or worse) hurled from residential tower blocks. The cold grey sky and colder Belfast Lough, from where on a clear day Scotland can be seen. <br /><br />As the hunt for the killer continues, we are given insights into both the culture and history of a wore-torn country. <i>The roof was thick slate and there were cast-iron grills on the windows. The front door was a massive oak affair with an iron lock. I knew from my history that the <b>badhuns</b> had large basements for storing food and grain and many of them were built over their own well or spring. You could easily survive a machine-gun or RPG attack and you’d do pretty well in the face of a zombie invasion, comet strike or the apocalypse…</i><br /><br />At times graphically violent, with low-level offensive language, this makes an interesting read, though I preferred one of the later titles in the series, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/26231518.Rain_Dogs__Detective_Sean_Duffy___5_" title="Rain Dogs (Detective Sean Duffy, #5) by Adrian McKinty" rel="nofollow noopener">Rain Dogs</a>.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3451397850897655443" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


