<div id="review_2541167950" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2541167950" />
    <a title="Kathleen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/47188780-kathleen"><img alt="Kathleen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1520288810p2/47188780.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2541167950?book_show_action=true">Sep 24, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kathleen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kathleen" href="/user/show/47188780-kathleen">Kathleen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2541167950" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2008665265096157716">This is my first McKinty crime novel and it will certainly not be my last. The man can write! [Winner of the Edgar Award in the U.S. and the Ned Kelly in Ireland.] This offering takes place in 1981 Northern Ireland through the eyes of Detective Sargeant Sean Duffy. McKinty peppers his tale with historical nuggets that transport the reader to the time of the Troubles when it was a powder keg. Bobby Sands has died in prison due to his hunger strike. There are frequent bombings and the Royal Ulster</span>
  <span id="freeText2008665265096157716" style="display:none">This is my first McKinty crime novel and it will certainly not be my last. The man can write! [Winner of the Edgar Award in the U.S. and the Ned Kelly in Ireland.] This offering takes place in 1981 Northern Ireland through the eyes of Detective Sargeant Sean Duffy. McKinty peppers his tale with historical nuggets that transport the reader to the time of the Troubles when it was a powder keg. Bobby Sands has died in prison due to his hunger strike. There are frequent bombings and the Royal Ulster Constabulary has to often travel in military style vehicles as the local Catholic population targets them by throwing projectiles and planting IEDs along the roads.<br /><br />In the midst of this chaos, a man is found dead. His body has been mutilated. And then another body is found with the same mutilation. Detective Sargeant believes that a serial killer is at work, taking advantage of the political situation to obscure his crimes. With that, McKinty’s complex plot takes off with a bang! Count on a lot of twists and turns. Sean Duffy is a Catholic, which makes him very unpopular with the IRA. But he is smart, funny and tenacious. I look forward to reading McKinty’s other offerings in this series. Recommend.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="2008665265096157716" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


